hw5

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • hw5.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends Object
    Graph represents a mutable mathematical graph data structure. All nodes and labeled edges are represented as Nodes and Edges. Please see their documentations. The graph is labeled: i.e. the edges are given labels. The graph is directed: i.e. there is a concept of direction with the edges. Finally, edges of a particular node are unique: there can be at most one outgoing edge from a node to another node with that particular name.
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Rohan Guliani
    Specification Fields
    • nodes - : list of all the nodes in the graph
    • edges - : list of outgoing edges for each node (containing the names of the nodes that the edges point to)

      • addEdge

        public boolean addEdge(Node key,
                       Node target,
                       String edgeName)
        Adds an outgoing edge from node key to node target.
        Parameters:
        key: - The node that the edge is to be added to.
        target: - The node on the receiving side of the edge.
        edgeName - The name to give to the edge
        Returns:
        true if successfully added or false if the graph didn't contain the node key or the graph did contain the key but the exact same edge (with same name) already existed
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if either key or target or edgeName is null
        Effects:
        adds a valid edge to this.nodes(key).edges if both key and target are valid (see @return branch)
        Modifies:
        this.nodes(key).edges, i.e. the edges field that corresponds to the node to which an edge is to be added.

      • addEdge

        public boolean addEdge(Edge newEdge)
        Adds an outgoing edge from node key to node target.
        Parameters:
        newEdge: - the Edge to be added
        Returns:
        true if successfully added or false if the graph didn't contain the node key or the graph did contain the key but the exact same edge (with same name) already existed
        Throws:

        Effects:

      • removeNode

        public boolean removeNode(Node node)
        Removes a node from the graph, as well as all the edges that were pointing to it.
        Parameters:
        node: - The node to be removed.
        Returns:
        true if the node was successfully removed or false if node was not valid.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if node is null.
        Effects:
        removes the given node from this.nodes and removes all edges in every node in the graph that pointed to the node that was removed.
        Modifies:
        this.nodes and this.nodes(n).edges for every node n in the graph.
